data.enText: to cause a particular reaction or have a particular effect

data.chText: 这个声明激起了抗议的风潮。
data.enText: The announcement provoked a storm of protest.

data.chText: 这篇文章旨在引发讨论。
data.enText: The article was intended to provoke discussion.

data.chText: 乳制品可能会引起某些人的过敏反应。
data.enText: Dairy products may provoke allergic reactions in some people.
to say or do sth that you know will annoy sb so that they react in an angry way

data.chText: 律师声称，他的当事人是受到被告的挑衅才采取暴力行动的。
data.enText: The lawyer claimed his client was provoked into acts of violence by the defendant.

data.chText: 说话要小心，他这个人一惹就火儿。
data.enText: Be careful what you say─he's easily provoked.

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+带to的不定式

simple_means.memory_skill: pro 在前 + vok 叫喊；声音 + e → 到别人面前喊叫，煽风点火 → 激怒；煽动

ex.chText: 如果不是被惹恼了，他是不会责骂你的。
ex.enText: He would not have scolded you if he hadn't been provoked.

ex.chText: 保罗坚持说他是因为被激怒才打架的。
ex.enText: Paul insisted that he was provoked into fighting.

synonyms.bx: 尤指故意激怒某人，含有挑衅之意。

ex.chText: 最让她生气的是他居然一句道歉的话都没有。
ex.enText: What angered her most was his total lack of apology.

ex.chText: 老师对他的谎话感到愤怒。
ex.enText: The teacher was angered by his lies.

synonyms.bx: 指激怒某人，其程度通常高于 annoy。

ex.chText: 他翻来覆去的发问让她非常生气。
ex.enText: She was annoyed by his repeated questions.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，程度较轻，强调不断地烦扰，尤指以重复性的行为让人心烦或恼火。

ex.chText: 请不要问些傻问题来烦我。
ex.enText: Don't badger me with your silly questions.

synonyms.bx: 强调没完没了的发问、噪音等惹人生气。

ex.enText: She is very busy; please don't bother her.

ex.chText: 对不起打扰你一下，到火车站怎么走？
ex.enText: I'm sorry to bother you, can you tell me the way to the station?

synonyms.bx: 主要侧重于动作、客观事物对人的搅扰，而不强调人的心理及思维方面。

ex.chText: 外面的嘈杂声让我睡不好觉。
ex.enText: The noise outside disturbed my sleep.

synonyms.bx: 常指打断他人的睡眠、工作等，语气较强。

ex.enText: The reporters wouldn't stop hounding him.

synonyms.bx: 尤指为获得某种东西（如信息、隐情等）而不停地追着骚扰某人。

ex.chText: 他周末总是中午才起床，真让我恼火。
ex.enText: It really irritates me when he gets up at noon at weekends.

synonyms.bx: 指因重复或长时间做某事而使人不快。

ex.chText: 妻子没完没了的抱怨真让他烦恼不已。
ex.enText: He was pestered with complaints from his wife.

synonyms.bx: 尤指不断地要求某人做某事，强调纠缠至其难以忍受的地步。

tr: evoke or provoke to appear or occur
example: Her behavior provoked a quarrel between the couple
He is known to harry his staff when he is overworked
This man harasses his female co-workers

value.def: If you provoke someone, you deliberately annoy them and try to make them behave aggressively.

example.ex: He started beating me when I was about fifteen but I didn't do anything to provoke him...
example.tran: 在我快15岁时他开始打我，可我并没有任何招惹他的举动。

example.ex: I provoked him into doing something really stupid.
example.tran: 在我的刺激下他做了件非常愚蠢的事。

value.def: If something provokes a reaction, it causes it.

example.ex: His election success has provoked a shocked reaction...
example.tran: 他的当选引起一片震惊。

example.ex: The destruction of the mosque has provoked anger throughout the Muslim world.
example.tran: 毁坏清真寺的行为激怒了整个伊斯兰世界。
